      "date": "2019-02-05 20:58:21.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nPS: it would also be good to change check_swap_layouts_support() from:\n\n        skip \"Does not support layout lock\"\n\nto\n\n        error \"Does not support layout lock?\"\n\nsince this has been available since Lustre 2.5 and we are not running 2.13 test scripts with servers older than this.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "126a77ef514ba404a709a8fe69f14ba18a6bb69d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2019-02-05 21:00:52.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> PS: it would also be good to change check_swap_layouts_support()\n > from:\n > \n > skip \"Does not support layout lock\"\n > \n > to\n > \n > error \"Does not support layout lock?\"\n > \n > since this has been available since Lustre 2.5 and we are not\n > running 2.13 test scripts with servers older than this.\n\nkeeping track of all such items is kind of hard though? And while it's highly unlikely any interop is going to be performed with 2.5 at this point, in the future such determination might be complicated?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "82c2373eeb561973bfcad6b9b0913c530e844f3a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2019-02-05 21:06:39.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> > PS: it would also be good to change check_swap_layouts_support()\n > > from:\n > >\n > > skip \"Does not support layout lock\"\n > >\n > > to\n > >\n > > error \"Does not support layout lock?\"\n > >\n > > since this has been available since Lustre 2.5 and we are not\n > > running 2.13 test scripts with servers older than this.\n > \n > keeping track of all such items is kind of hard though? And while\n > it's highly unlikely any interop is going to be performed with 2.5\n > at this point, in the future such determination might be\n > complicated?\n\nIf/when such a day arrives where we don't have layout swap in the future we can look at it again.  \n\nI'd rather avoid current situation where tests are silently skipped for *current* releases to handle the hypothetical case of interop testing with some ancient or far future release.  The \"skip\" was fine when this feature was first added in 2013 (commit v2_3_63_0-6-gead6f5b2b5) because interop tests with 2.1/2.2 would have failed, but I think it is more of a danger today than a benefit.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
